  "text": "Garmin Instinct 2 Solar $229 $400 Save $171 The Garmin Instinct 2 Solar is the perfect smartwatch for anyone who is active and hates the idea of charging their watch. This rugged smartwatch is now down to its lowest price at $229. If you're looking for a new smartwatch that's easy to use and feature-packed, then the Garmin Instinct 2 Solar is going to be it. This smartwatch is rugged, while also featuring fantastic battery life thanks to its solar charging capabilities. Furthermore, it can now be had at a steep discount that knocks the price down to just $229. This is the lowest price we've seen on this watch, so get it now while you still can. Related What's great about the Garmin Instinct 2 Solar? For the most part, you're going to get a pretty solid smartwatch with the Instinct 2 Solar. But the real highlight of this watch is that it delivers up to 28 days of battery life on a single charge. Furthermore, if you manage to get it charged via solar each day, it can last forever without having to be plugged in. This is a huge perk, especially if you're someone that's always on the go, and maybe can't plug in to charge the watch. When it comes to the design, this watch isn't all that elegant, but it does pack a rugged design with a fiber-reinforced polymer case that's meant to take on whatever you can throw at it. It has a monochrome transflective memory-in-pixel display that looks good in most conditions, and it also features a variety of sensors that can track your health and fitness metrics. You can also get a better picture thanks to the watch's ability to track your sleep quality and stress levels. You can even accurately track your hikes and jogs using multi-band GNSS, and get more detailed information about your whereabouts thanks to the built-in compass and barometric altimeter. While the watch comes pretty packed with features, you will have the ability to expand using the Garmin Connect IQ Store. And since this is a smartwatch, you'll get notifications on your wrist when connected to a smartphone. Just in case you ever leave your wallet at home, you can use Garmin Pay at compatible terminals to make purchases. For the most part, this is just a superb watch that gets a lot of things right. And you can't really complain thanks to its recent price drop.",
